25/08/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- The Central Election Commission voted on Thursday (24 August) on rules for forming local election commissions to oversee the upcoming winter elections. The Democratic Party (DP), the New Democrat Party, the Republican Party, the Socialist Party (SP) and the Socialist Movement for Integration will have members in the local commissions. The seventh member will be selected by lot between the ruling DP and the opposition SP. (Albanian News - 25/08/06)
